OL,4,C'terrified' of speaking out after
OL,5,Carrest
OL,7,FA number of us have already been put
OL,8,Fthrough aggressive safeguarding
OL,9,Fprocesses - only to be exonerated. We
OL,10,Fhave not recovered from the trauma of
OL,11,Fthese processes and the repeated
OL,12,FStates debates, which have re-hashed
OL,13,Fthis topic and turned our lives into a
OL,14,Fpolitical football, have only
OL,15,Fretraumatised us. You cannot imagine
OL,16,Fhow terrifying it is to speak out -
OL,17,Feven more so now that there is a
OL,18,Fthreat of Police action for doing so.
OL,20,FThese are truly worrying times for
OL,21,Ffree speech.
